        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 1 at 5:02PM EDT until August 1 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 7 miles southwest of Salisbury to 7 miles northwest of
Kannapolis to 3 miles southwest of Huntersville, moving southeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Cornelius, Davidson, Ramsey Creek Park, Piedmont Research Station,
Mooresville, Huntersville, and Lake Norman.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
